  <section>
    <info>
      <title>Introduction</title>
    </info>

    <para>The Docbkx Wrapper Plugin wraps the <link
    xlink:href="http://docbkx-tools.sourceforge.net/docbkx-maven-plugin/">docbkx-maven-plugin</link>
    and the <link
    xlink:href="http://khuxtable.github.com/htmlfilter-site-maven-plugin">htmlfilter-site-maven-plugin</link>
    such that they easily produce Maven site documentation from <link
    xlink:href="http://www.docbook.org">DocBook</link> source that will fit in
    with the <link
    xlink:href="http://maven.apache.org/doxia/">Doxia</link>-generated site
    reports produced by the <link
    xlink:href="http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-site-plugin/">site
    plugin</link>.</para>

    <section>
      <info>
        <title>Goals Overview</title>
      </info>

      <para>The Docbkx Wrapper Plugin has one goal:</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para><link
          xlink:href="generate-mojo.html">docbkx-wrapper:generate</link> runs
          <link
          xlink:href="http://docbkx-tools.sourceforge.net/docbkx-maven-plugin/generate-html-mojo.html">docbkx:generate-xhtml</link>
          and then runs <link
          xlink:href="http://khuxtable.github.com/htmlfilter-site-maven-plugin/generate-mojo.html">htmlfilter-site:merge</link>
          on the resulting files.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </section>

    <section>
      <info>
        <title>Usage</title>
      </info>

      <para>Information on using the Docbkx Wrapper Plugin can be found on the
      <link xlink:href="usage.html">usage</link> page.</para>
    </section>
